  "_meta": {
    "description": "TradingView parity reference values. Pulled manually from TV charts. Used by tests/test_indicators.py::TestTradingViewParity once populated.",
    "indicator_params": {
      "rsi": {"length": 14, "source": "close"},
      "macd": {"fast": 12, "slow": 26, "signal": 9, "source": "close", "ma_type": "EMA"},
      "adx_dmi": {"adx_smoothing": 14, "di_length": 14},
      "bollinger": {"length": 20, "stdev": 2.0, "source": "close"},
      "supertrend": {"atr_length": 10, "factor": 3.0},
      "stochastic": {"length_k": 14, "smooth_k": 3, "smooth_d": 3},
      "mfi": {"length": 14},
      "atr": {"length": 14, "smoothing": "RMA"},
      "obv": {"source": "close"},
      "cmf": {"length": 20}
    },
    "tolerances": {
      "rsi": "abs <= 0.10",
      "macd_*": "rel <= 0.05%",
      "adx_*": "abs <= 0.50",
      "bollinger_*": "rel <= 0.01%",
      "supertrend_value": "rel <= 0.10%",
      "supertrend_direction": "exact match",
      "stoch_*": "abs <= 0.20",
      "mfi": "abs <= 0.20",
      "atr": "rel <= 0.05%",
      "obv": "exact (integer-valued)",
      "cmf": "abs <= 0.005"
    },
    "instructions": [
      "1. Copy this file to tv_reference_values.json before editing — the .template.json is the canonical starting point and should stay all-null.",
      "2. For each fixture key below, replace `null` values with what TradingView's Data Window shows for that bar timestamp.",
      "3. Pull values for AT LEAST the last 3 bars; expand to 10 when you have time.",
      "4. Direction values for supertrend: +1 when green/uptrend, -1 when red/downtrend.",
      "5. Skip an entire indicator (delete its block) if you can't add it on TV. The parity test will only assert against keys you provide."
    ]
  },

